''' Tripura ''' ([[Bengal-ngî]]: '''ত্রিপুরা''', [[Là-tên sṳ-mû]] chón-siá: {{Unicode|Tripura}}) he Yin-thu ke yit-ke pâng, vi-yî [[Yin-thu tûng-pet-phu]], pâng ke nàm-piên lâu Bangladesh chiap-yòng. Hien Tripura Sú-fú vì [[Agartala]] ([[:en:Agartala|Agartala]]), kôn-fông ngî-ngièn vi [[Bengal-ngî]] fò [[Kokborok-ngî]] ([[:en:Kokborok language|Kokborok language]], fe̍t chhṳ̍t-chiap chhṳ̂n thi̍t lî phú ngî). Tripura ke yit-ke nui-liu̍k pâng, thi-lî thi̍t-chṳ̂n he yù kí ke nàm-pet Sân-mak chûng-kiên ke sân kuk, lâu sî-phu phìn-ngièn ke chhong-thai. Chú-yeu chûng-kau vì [[Yin-thu kau]] [[sin li̍t phai]], séu-sú ngìn sin-ngióng Yî-sṳ̂-làn-kau, Kî-tuk-kau fe̍t fu̍t-kau. 
Mien-chit: 10,492 phìn-fông kûng-lî, [[ngìn-khiéu]]: 2.8 pak van (1991).
